    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided document chunks, the segment reporting disclosures can be summarized as follows. No discussion of inter-segment transaction treatment appears in the excerpts supplied, so that disclosure is absent.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Identification of Reportable Segments\nThe company operates three reportable segments:  \n- **Space**  \n- **Connectivity**  \n- **AI**  \n\nThese were realigned following the Mergers and are the segments used by the Chief Executive Officer (CODM) to assess performance and allocate resources based on segment income (loss) from operations.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Segment Revenue and Segment Profit/Loss (Income from Operations)\nSegment revenue and income (loss) from operations are presented in both narrative highlights and tabular formats. The most complete tables are the 2023 segment income statement table (shown below) and the various reconciliation tables that show income from operations and adjusted EBITDA.\n\n**Year Ended December 31, 2023 (from note table)**\n| ($ millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n|--------------|-------|--------------|----|---------------------------|\n| Revenue | 3,557 | 3,869 | 2,961 | 10,387 |\n| Income (loss) from operations | (1) | 469 | (3,973) | (3,505) |\n\nOther periods provide segment income (loss) from operations through the reconciliation tables and narrative:\n\n| Period | Segment | Revenue | Income (Loss) from Operations |\n|--------|---------|---------|-------------------------------|\n| Q1 2026 | Space | $619\u202fM* | $(662)\u202fM |\n|         | Connectivity | $3,257\u202fM* | $1,188\u202fM |\n|         | AI | $818\u202fM* | $(2,469)\u202fM |\n| FY 2025 | Space | $4,086\u202fM* | $(657)\u202fM |\n|         | Connectivity | $11,387\u202fM* | $4,423\u202fM |\n|         | AI | $3,201\u202fM* | $(6,355)\u202fM |\n| FY 2024 | Space | — | $21\u202fM |\n|         | Connectivity | — | $2,006\u202fM |\n|         | AI | — | $(1,561)\u202fM |\n| FY 2023 | Space | $3,557\u202fM | $(1)\u202fM |\n|         | Connectivity | $3,869\u202fM | $469\u202fM |\n|         | AI | $2,961\u202fM | $(3,973)\u202fM |\n\n* Revenue figures for 2025 and Q1 2026 appear in the narrative summaries; income from operations figures are from the segment Adjusted EBITDA reconciliation tables.\n\nAdditionally, a Space-only table gives income from operations and Adjusted EBITDA for multiple years without revenue.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Adjusted EBITDA\nSegment Adjusted EBITDA is a key non-GAAP measure for each segment. The document provides reconciliations from segment income (loss) from operations to Segment Adjusted EBITDA for every period presented, adding back depreciation & amortization, share-based compensation, restructuring charges, and impairment.\n\n**Segment Adjusted EBITDA ($ millions) – from reconciliation tables and narrative:**\n\n| Period | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n|--------|-------|--------------|----|---------------------------|\n| **Q1 2026** | $(351) | $2,087 | $(609) | $1,127 |\n| **Q1 2025** | $224 | $1,618 | $(112) | $1,730 |\n| **FY 2025** | $653 | $7,168 | $(1,237) | $6,584 |\n| **FY 2024** | $1,154 | $3,849 | $347 | $5,350 |\n| **FY 2023** | $997 | $1,602 | $1,222 | $3,821 |\n\nThe Space Exploration segment also provides Segment Adjusted EBITDA in an unaudited operating data table (without Connectivity/AI context):\n- Q1 2026: $(351)\u202fM  \n- Q1 2025: $224\u202fM  \n- FY 2025: $653\u202fM  \n- FY 2024: $1,154\u202fM  \n- FY 2023: $997\u202fM\n\n---\n\n### 4. Treatment of Inter-Segment Transactions\n**No information about how inter-segment transactions are treated is present in the provided chunks.** None of the excerpts contain language about elimination, transfer pricing, or intersegment revenues/costs. The segment reporting note introduction (chunk 29) only states that tables follow for revenues, significant expenses, and income from operations, but no further detail is given on inter-se