n Operating Income:**  \n  In the Management’s Discussion and Analysis, the increase in Connectivity’s cost of revenue and the partial offset to operating income growth are repeatedly attributed to higher depreciation from these capitalized launch costs. For example:  \n  “...partially offset by higher depreciation of capitalized launch and satellite costs due to the increase in Starlink flights…”  \n  And, in a quarterly comparison:  \n  “Cost of revenue … increased … primarily due to higher depreciation of $276 million from capitalized launch and satellite costs…”  \n\nIn summary, the Space segment performs launches for Starlink, but rather than booking revenue, it capitalizes the launch costs (including flight vehicle allocation) into the satellite assets under PP&E. The Connectivity segment then depreciates those assets over their useful lives, with the depreciation expense recorded in its cost of revenue, thereby impacting segment profitability.',
